#week-title("Three", "Designing the Personal Alchemical Spread")

=== Core Teaching

The personal alchemical spread, introduced in Year Two Month 6, is now revised
and deepened for the Adept level. At the Year Two level, the spread reviewed
the Plant Stone work in retrospect. At the Adept level, the spread is a
forward-looking diagnostic instrument for the ongoing mineral work.

The Adept's spread is not prescribed — it emerges from the practitioner's own
understanding of the Work's current structure. This is itself a test: a student
who cannot design a spread that meaningfully maps their mineral Work has not
yet internalised the Tarot–Tree–alchemical correspondence system deeply enough
for Adept-level use.

*Principles for the Adept's spread design:*
- Every position should correspond to a specific aspect of the current Work —
  not a generic psychological question but an operative alchemical question.
- The positions should trace the Work's movement through time: current state,
  what has been accomplished, what is the next operation, what is blocking
  progress, what the preparation is calling for.
- Include at minimum one position for the inner Work's current state alongside
  the outer laboratory work.
- The World card appearing in a central or culminating position is read as a
  sign that the Work is approaching a completion of this phase — not of the
  overall Stone, but of the current cycle.

*Mapping the mineral Work to the Tree.* Which sephiroth are most active in the
current preparations?
- Binah (Saturn): the restriction and crystallisation of the mineral Salt
- Geburah (Mars): calcination, the burning away of impurity
- Hod (Mercury): the analytical observation of fractions, the laboratory journal
- Yesod (Moon): the Via Humida dissolution cycles; the lunar vehicle
- Malkuth (Earth): the physical preparation in hand; the sealed flask

Designing the spread around these active sephiroth gives the layout an alchemical
architecture rather than a generic divinatory structure.

=== Topics This Week

- Principles for designing the Adept-level alchemical spread
- Mapping the current mineral Work to the active sephiroth on the Tree
- Reading the World card in the context of a mineral Work spread
- The spread as a quarterly diagnostic instrument

#inner-work[
  *Designing and Conducting the Spread*

  Design your personal alchemical spread for the current mineral Work.
  Write out each position and what it addresses before drawing the cards.
  Then conduct the reading.

  Write a full interpretation of the spread in your Tarot journal. Pay
  particular attention to: the card at the position representing the next
  operation, and any card that appears at a position representing a blockage.
  These two positions often contain the most direct guidance the spread offers.
]

